item.title: CVE-2016-9586|2024-08-06T02:59:02.246Z -- redhat -- curl
item.description: curl before version 7.52.0 is vulnerable to a buffer overflow when doing a large floating point output in libcurl's implementation of the printf() functions. If there are any application that accepts a format string from the outside without necessary input filtering, it could allow remote attacks.
